	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=220288><span id=Scholar>Lord Raksus</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>36 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.05]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>---<br>If you look under the &quot;Haste&quot; description you'll see Level for Effect: 35 thus there is &quot;some&quot; level restriction on it.<br>---<br><br>No, not really.&nbsp;&nbsp;First, don't believe everything you read.  Second, haste is capped.  Since this is 36% haste, the first level you get the <b>full</b> effect is 35.  As I recall, the cap pre-50 is your level +1.  So if you put this on a level 20, it'll be 21% haste (until he levels, of course).  It's more of a &quot;recommended level&quot; than a &quot;required level&quot; for the effect.  Not that it matters since it's nerfed to required 55 now.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
